request.description:
Generate a new schedule for the given classes. Body typically includes classIds and generation options. Returns generated schedule data.

{  
"classIds": \["class-uuid-1", "class-uuid-2"\],  
"subjectTeachers": {  
"taks": \["teacher-uuid-1", "teacher-uuid-2"\],  
"al7an": \["teacher-uuid-3"\],  
"coptic": \["teacher-uuid-4"\]  
}  
}

Validate and apply a proposed schedule. Body: rows array of { classId, slot, subject, teacherId }. Does not persist to DB; use Save Schedule to persist.

{  
"rows": \[  
{  
"class": { "id": "class-uuid-1", "location": "فصل 1", "level": { "level": 1, "stage": 1 } },  
"A": { "subject": "taks", "teacherId": "teacher-uuid-1" },  
"B": { "subject": "al7an", "teacherId": "teacher-uuid-2" },  
"C": { "subject": "coptic", "teacherId": "teacher-uuid-3" }  
},  
{  
"class": { "id": "class-uuid-2", "location": "فصل 2", "level": { "level": 1, "stage": 2 } },  
"A": { "subject": "al7an", "teacherId": "teacher-uuid-2" },  
"B": { "subject": "coptic", "teacherId": "teacher-uuid-3" },  
"C": { "subject": "taks", "teacherId": "teacher-uuid-1" }  
}  
\]  
}
